Source: UIUC Airfoil Coordinates Database (Selig / UIUC Applied Aerodynamics
Group), fetched verbatim on 2026-07-21:

    https://m-selig.ae.illinois.edu/ads/coord/clarky.dat

clarky.dat is stored byte-for-byte as fetched (Lednicer format: title line,
"n_upper n_lower" counts, then two blocks of x/c, y/c pairs each running
0 -> 1, upper first then lower). Verified with two independent fetches
(identical) plus a sanity check against the published Clark Y
characteristics: max thickness ~11.6% c near x/c = 0.36 and max camber
~3.4% c near x/c = 0.42, both consistent with the commonly cited 11.7%/3.55%
figures for this section (small cross-source digitization variance is
expected). Do not hand-edit; re-fetch and diff if this file is ever
regenerated.

Used by src/conceptual_design/prop_geometry.py (adr/0017) as the reference
propeller blade section, thickness-scaled per radial station.
